Description: Emergency Medical Information
Full Description: miCARD is a company dedicated to preparing individuals and families for an unexpected medical emergency. The company was founded in 2007 by James Kelley, an emergency physician, and his brother Michael Kelley, a website design and advertising professional. Years of caring for patients in critical medical situations with limited information, led Dr. Kelley to develop the miCARD solution for emergency preparedness. Our goal at miCARD is simple: Give our customers the tools to help their doctors deliver better care. Because most individuals receive healthcare through a fragmented network of providers and care settings, miCARD strives to serve an immediate and practical need for individual control and oversight of one's vital medical information with an emphasis on preparedness against the unanticipated medical emergency. Experience in the use and gathering of information during emergency medical care has led us to develop miCARD, a system built to benefit each of us by providing doctors and care providers with the information needed most, when time is crucial and optimal care requires it.  miCARD is a socially aware company, and our affiliations with select partner organizations are designed to help individuals improve their personal health outcomes while benefiting others through cause awareness and charitable funding. We seek your participation in this effort and welcome any suggestions for alignment in partnership or charitable relations.

Full Description: Trans Web Global is a consulting practice focused on experience-based university admission counseling, introducing students to the opportunities, training, and review needed for an exceptional post-secondary education while advancing the dialogue of a global education. Transitions Web Global is an education consulting practice that specializes in admissions counseling and competence development to ensure a higher quality of post-secondary education for students.  Since its inception in 2009, the transitions lab group has worked unwaveringly towards assisting students in achieving their goals. Our mission is to develop a personalized programme for each individual student to not only ensure their admission into their institution of choice but to also guarantee that they thrive in a global campus and achieve the goals they set out for themselves. Behind all of these activities and services is a dedicated team of trained individuals to ensure each student receives the required attention and opportunities to guide them along the admission process. Our team consists of a number of practiced and trained counselors and educators. These members are also actively working on various research projects and remain deeply involved in their community as leaders and activists. We at transitions lab strongly believe in the importance of youth and as a result, employ many students. This amalgamation of student leaders and experienced teachers creates a dynamic and fascinating work environment. With almost a decade of work under our belt, we are proud of the quality and professional guidance that we have provided to thousands of students around the world. As a result of our consistent service, we have achieved recognition and awards from a number of institutions such as the University of Waterloo, University of Texas and American Scholastic Math Association etc. Despite this, the greatest reward for us at Transitions lab is in ensuring the acceptance of students in their desired university and giving them the opportunities to strive in a global environment.

Their team provides both clients and clients' customers with personal care and attention, resulting in increased revenue for the business.
